The loan for borrower Kenji Park has failed the credit score requirement, as his score is 607, which is below the minimum threshold of 620 for conventional loans. This requirement, outlined in OSFI B-20 Section 4, is designed to ensure that borrowers have a sufficient credit history and financial responsibility to manage their mortgage obligations. The breach poses a risk to the institution as it may lead to higher default rates, impacting the overall portfolio quality and potentially increasing financial losses.

**CONTROL_3 — Stress Test**  
This loan has also failed to meet the stress test requirement, as the borrower did not pass the minimum qualifying rate stress test, which mandates that the contract rate plus 2% must be met. According to OSFI B-20 Section 2, this requirement is crucial for assessing a borrower''s ability to withstand potential interest rate increases and ensure they can continue to make payments under adverse conditions. The failure to comply with this control increases the risk of borrower default, which could result in significant financial implications for the institution and undermine its lending practices.', 'High') ON CONFLICT (result_id) DO NOTHING;
