INSERT INTO public.compliance_results (result_id, loan_id, checked_at, control_results, compliance_score, overall_status, breach_explanations, severity) VALUES ('19e64625-3451-4039-a632-45d5f1e35e15', 'LN-10038', '2026-02-25T21:08:37.487282', '{''control_1'': False, ''control_2'': True, ''control_3'': True, ''control_4'': True, ''control_5'': False, ''control_6'': False, ''control_7'': True, ''control_8'': True, ''control_9'': False, ''control_10'': True}', 6, 'BREACH', '**CONTROL_1 — DTI Ratio Check**  
The loan for borrower Lin Tanaka has a Debt-to-Income (DTI) ratio of 50.20%, exceeding the regulatory requirement of 44%. This requirement, as outlined in OSFI B-20 credit risk guidelines, is designed to ensure that borrowers do not take on excessive debt relative to their income, thereby reducing the risk of default. The breach poses a significant risk to the institution as it may lead to increased default rates, impacting the overall loan portfolio quality and financial stability.

**CONTROL_5 — Employment Verification Timeliness**  
Employment verification for Lin Tanaka was not completed within the required timeframe of 10 days prior to closing. According to OSFI B-20 Section 3, timely verification of employment is crucial to confirm the borrower''s ability to meet mortgage obligations. This breach increases the risk of lending to a borrower whose employment status may have changed, potentially leading to repayment issues and financial losses for the institution.

**CONTROL_6 — Fair Lending Review**  
A documented fair lending review was not completed for this loan prior to funding, which is a requirement under OSFI B-20 Section 6. This review is essential to ensure compliance with fair lending practices and to prevent discriminatory lending. The absence of this review poses a risk of regulatory penalties and reputational damage to the institution, as it may indicate a failure to uphold fair lending standards.

**CONTROL_9 — Dual Underwriter Review**  
The loan amount of $1,382,500.22 exceeds the threshold of $750,000, necessitating a dual underwriter review as per OSFI B-20 Section 5. This requirement is in place to provide an additional layer of scrutiny for high-value loans, ensuring that the underwriting process is robust and mitigates risk. The lack of a dual review increases the risk of inadequate assessment of the loan''s creditworthiness, which could lead to higher default rates and financial exposure for the institution.', 'Medium') ON CONFLICT (result_id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.compliance_results (result_id, loan_id, checked_at, control_results, compliance_score, overall_status, breach_explanations, severity) VALUES ('20d05861-f5bf-4c57-a229-8cc12afb66f2', 'LN-10018', '2026-02-25T21:38:49.638326', '{''control_1'': True, ''control_2'': True, ''control_3'': True, ''control_4'': True, ''control_5'': True, ''control_6'': True, ''control_7'': True, ''control_8'': False, ''control_9'': True, ''control_10'': True}', 9, 'BREACH', '**CONTROL_8 — Closing Disclosure Timing**  
The closing disclosure for Megan Santos'' FHA loan was not sent at least 3 business days prior to the closing date, which constitutes a breach of compliance control. The regulatory requirement mandates that borrowers receive the closing disclosure in a timely manner to ensure they have adequate time to review the terms of the loan and understand their financial obligations. This requirement exists to protect consumers and promote transparency in the mortgage process. The risk posed by this breach includes potential delays in the closing process, which could lead to borrower dissatisfaction and damage the institution''s reputation, as well as potential regulatory scrutiny and penalties for failing to adhere to federal mortgage disclosure rules.', 'Low') ON CONFLICT (result_id) DO NOTHING;
