The loan for Neha Johnson failed the stress test requirement, as the borrower did not meet the minimum qualifying rate of the contract rate plus 2%. According to OSFI B-20 Section 2, all borrowers must pass this stress test to ensure they can manage potential increases in interest rates. This breach poses a significant risk to the institution, as it may lead to higher default rates if borrowers are unable to sustain their mortgage payments under increased financial pressure.

**CONTROL_4 — Income Verification**  
This loan is non-compliant with the income verification requirement, as only one independent income document is on file, whereas at least two are mandated by OSFI B-20 Section 3. This requirement exists to ensure that the borrower''s income is adequately verified and reliable, reducing the risk of lending to borrowers who may not have sufficient income to support their mortgage obligations. The lack of proper income verification increases the risk of default, potentially leading to financial losses for the institution.

**CONTROL_6 — Fair Lending Review**  
The fair lending review for Neha Johnson''s loan was not completed prior to funding, which is a violation of OSFI B-20 Section 6. This requirement is in place to ensure that lending practices are equitable and do not discriminate against any borrower based on prohibited grounds. The absence of a documented fair lending review exposes the institution to reputational risk and potential regulatory scrutiny, as it raises concerns about compliance with fair lending laws and the possibility of discriminatory lending practices.', 'High') ON CONFLICT (result_id) DO NOTHING;
