The loan for borrower Matthew Davis has failed the credit score requirement, as his score is 611, which is below the minimum threshold of 620 for conventional loans as stipulated in OSFI B-20 Section 4 — Borrower Assessment. This requirement exists to ensure that borrowers have a sufficient credit history and financial responsibility, reducing the risk of default. The breach poses a significant risk to the institution, as lending to borrowers with lower credit scores can lead to higher default rates, impacting the overall financial stability and risk profile of the institution.

**CONTROL_8 — Closing Disclosure Timing**  
This loan has also failed to meet the requirement for closing disclosure timing, as the disclosure must be sent at least 3 business days before closing, which has not been confirmed in this case. This regulatory requirement is in place to ensure that borrowers have adequate time to review the terms and conditions of their mortgage, promoting transparency and informed decision-making. Failure to comply with this requirement increases the risk of borrower dissatisfaction and potential legal repercussions for the institution, as it undermines the integrity of the mortgage lending process.', 'High') ON CONFLICT (result_id) DO NOTHING;
